THREE people died when a minibus taxi crashed into a stationary truck yesterday morning. The acccident happened on the N4 toll road near Schoonspruit farm, between Marloth Park and Komatipoort in Mpumalanga, at about 5am. According to community safety spokesman Moeti Mmusi, the taxi rammed into the side of the truck in the emergency lane. Mmusi said three people died at the scene while the other three sustained moderate injuries.  They were rushed to the nearest hospital. “Both vehicles were travelling towards Komatipoort and are registered in Mozambique,” Mmusi told the People’s Paper. “We believe the minibus taxi was travelling from Joburg to Maputo. “At the moment, it’s not clear what may have caused the crash.” He said investigations are under way.